<br>
I thought I read something about Verant changing their character database structure however, so perhaps this will change... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/25/02 1:40:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10845.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on +Skill Mod items</span><hr size=1> According to popular thought at EQTraders...  Skill Mod items stack additively, not cumulatively.<br>
<br>
Thus the Belt from Sanctus that gives +10% Smithing and the Geerlok Smithing Hammer that gives +5% Smithing would give a total of +15% Smithing.<br>
<br>
So a character with 200 Smithing skill would end up with 230 (200 * (1.10 + 1.05)) not 231 ((200 * 1.10 * 1.05). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upricklypeete.showPublicProfile?language=EN>pricklypeete</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/25/02 2:10:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10845.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on +Skill Mod items</span><hr size=1> i have a 3% meditate item and a 4% meditate item on a level 32 twink (med skill 165 i think)<br>
<br>
he gets 12 mana/tick from medding with neither of em on, with the 3% one on, with the 4% one on and 12 mana/tick with both on.<br>
<br>
i would've thought that if they stacked that it would've been enough to make it not round down to 0, but it's not conclusive. i'll put a few more levels on him and try it again...<br>
